1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,950
AI fluency can look impressive and still produce bad work.

2
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:09,778
Someone writes elaborate prompts, uses AI all day, and accepts a polished answer in seconds.

3
00:00:09,778 --> 00:00:11,961
The activity looks advanced.

4
00:00:11,961 --> 00:00:13,990
The judgment may be missing.

5
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:17,105
The better measure is not how often you use AI.

6
00:00:17,105 --> 00:00:25,346
It is whether you can decide when to involve it, explain the job clearly, evaluate what comes back, and take responsibility for what happens next.

7
00:00:25,346 --> 00:00:32,615
Those four abilities form the 4D AI Fluency Framework: Delegation, Description, Discernment, and Diligence.

8
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:34,471
They are human skills.

9
00:00:34,471 --> 00:00:38,413
A stronger model can help, but it cannot remove the need for them.

10
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:42,480
In this video, we will turn the four dimensions into a practical loop.

11
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:49,432
You will learn the decision behind each one, the common failure it prevents, and a reusable self-check for your next real task.

12
00:00:49,432 --> 00:00:54,048
Keep one idea in view: fluency is not a performance of clever prompting.

13
00:00:54,048 --> 00:00:58,230
It is the ability to move from intent to evidence without giving up judgment.
